Kubernetes Service Types - Quick Notes 

1. ClusterIP (Default Service) 

Purpose 

Exposes the application only inside the Kubernetes cluster. 

How to get ClusterIP 

kubectl get svc 
 

Example: 

NAME         TYPE        CLUSTER-IP 
my-service   ClusterIP   10.104.108.138 
 

How to test 

SSH into Minikube: 

minikube ssh 
 

Access Service: 

curl http://10.104.108.138:80/demo 
 

Traffic Flow 

Client Inside Cluster 
       ↓ 
ClusterIP:80 
       ↓ 
TargetPort:8000 
       ↓ 
Pod 
 

Important 

ClusterIP = Service Testing 
Pod IP     = Pod Testing 
 

Example Pod Test: 

curl http://10.244.0.6:8000/demo 
 

This bypasses the Service completely. 

 

2. NodePort 

Purpose 

Exposes the application on a Kubernetes Node. 

How to get Node IP 

minikube ip 
 

Example: 

192.168.49.2 
 

How to get NodePort 

kubectl get svc 
 

Example: 

NAME              TYPE       PORT(S) 
my-service-node   NodePort   80:30007/TCP 
 

Where: 

Service Port = 80 
NodePort     = 30007 
 

How to test 

curl http://192.168.49.2:30007/demo 
 

Traffic Flow 

NodeIP:30007 
       ↓ 
Service:80 
       ↓ 
TargetPort:8000 
       ↓ 
Pod 
 

 

3. LoadBalancer 

Purpose 

Exposes the application externally using a cloud provider load balancer. 

Used in: 

Amazon EKS 

Azure Kubernetes Service 

Google Kubernetes Engine 

How to get LoadBalancer IP 

kubectl get svc 
 

Example: 

NAME              TYPE           EXTERNAL-IP 
my-service-load   LoadBalancer   54.x.x.x 
 

or 

my-service-load   LoadBalancer   abc123.elb.amazonaws.com 
 

How to test 

curl http://<external-ip>/demo 
 

Traffic Flow 

Public IP / DNS 
       ↓ 
Load Balancer 
       ↓ 
Service 
       ↓ 
Pod 
 

 

4. LoadBalancer in Minikube 

Problem 

kubectl get svc 
 

Shows: 

EXTERNAL-IP   <pending> 
 

Reason 

Minikube has no cloud provider to create a real Load Balancer. 

Solution 

Run: 

minikube tunnel 
 

Then: 

kubectl get svc 
 

Example: 

NAME              TYPE           CLUSTER-IP       EXTERNAL-IP 
my-service-load   LoadBalancer   10.100.156.52    10.100.156.52 
 

How to get LoadBalancer IP in Minikube 

kubectl get svc 
 

Read the EXTERNAL-IP column. 

Example: 

10.100.156.52 
 

How to test 

From Minikube/cluster network: 

curl http://10.100.156.52:80/demo 
 

Important 

This is not a real public IP. 

minikube tunnel simulates LoadBalancer behavior locally. 

 

Useful Commands 

Get Pods 

kubectl get pods -o wide 
 

Shows: 

POD IP 
 

Example: 

10.244.0.6 
 

 

Get Services 

kubectl get svc 
 

Shows: 

CLUSTER-IP 
EXTERNAL-IP 
PORTS 
 

 

Get Node IP 

minikube ip 
 

Example: 

192.168.49.2 
 

 

Easy Memory Trick 

Pod IP 
↓ 
Tests Pod directly 
 
ClusterIP 
↓ 
Tests Service inside cluster 
 
NodeIP + NodePort 
↓ 
Tests Service through node 
 
LoadBalancer IP 
↓ 
Tests Service from outside world
